<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sandra W. Meyer has been appointed to head a newly created Office of Corporate 
Affairs at New York's Citicorp, the nation's largest banking company. The 
office will direct worldwide advertising, public affairs, press communications 
and investor relations. 
</P>
<P>
Meyer, who will take the Citicorp position on Feb. 20, is a managing director 
at Russell Reynolds Associates, an executive search firm. 
</P>
<P>
Citibank said Meyer will rank as a senior executive. The new office is part of 
an attempt by Chairman John S. Reed to improve the bank's external 
communications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
