<P>
MOORPARK RUNS CONFERENCE STREAK TO 20 WINS DESPITE LOSS OF MARSHALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RALPH NICHOLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Moorpark College women's basketball team, playing without Kerrie Marshall, 
its leading scorer and rebounder, extended its Western State Conference winning 
streak to 20 games over the last 3 seasons with a 75-54 victory over College of 
the Canyons on Tuesday at Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
Marshall left the team after a dispute with Coach Gary Abraham after she was 
late for practice Tuesday, according to Abraham. She was averaging 18 points 
and 8 rebounds a game to lead the Lady Raiders in both categories. 
</P>
<P>
"I hope we can pick up the slack with Kerrie gone," Abraham said. "It's no 
doubt a big loss for us." 
</P>
<P>
Susie Smiley scored 17 points to lead Moorpark (17-4, 5-0 in conference play). 
</P>
<P>
Mary Bittner added 13 and Kristie Sterbens had 10. 
</P>
<P>
Tressie Millender scored a game-high 32 points to lead Canyons (3-12, 2-3). 
RALPH NICHOLS 
