<P>
PLAN TO AID QUAKE VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
6A committee appointed by Pasadena Mayor William Thomson to recommend ways the 
city can help victims of the earthquake in Armenia has proposed that the city 
sponsor a Pasadena Crusade for the Children of Armenia. 
</P>
<P>
George Van Alstine, who headed the committee and is also chairman of the 
Pasadena Commission on Children and Youth, recommended that the city support a 
fund-raising effort to help children in Leninaken, a city of 200,000 that was 
badly damaged by the Dec. 7 earthquake. Artificial limbs and psychological 
counseling are needed, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The Board of Directors delayed action on the recommendation until Jan. 31 to 
coordinate plans with the Tournament of Roses Assn., which is also considering 
a fund-raising effort for earthquake victims. 
</P>
