<TEXT>
<P>
A crowd of Nicaraguans looted a Red Cross warehouse in Managua, taking aid 
packages intended for victims of Hurricane Joan, which struck the region in 
October, the opposition newspaper La Prensa and a Red Cross spokeswoman said. 
La Prensa reported that about 150 people gathered outside the warehouse in a 
poor neighborhood. Several youths then broke in and began tossing out boxes of 
clothing and food. 
</P>
