<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
VETERAN COUNCILMAN RECOVERING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Veteran Redondo Beach Councilman Archie Snow is undergoing treatment for heart 
ailments at Little Company of Mary Hospital in Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
City officials said Snow was admitted Jan. 4 after suffering a mild heart 
attack. An angioplasty was performed to clear a partly blocked artery, they 
said, and further tests were ordered Jan. 11 when the 70-year-old councilman 
began to experience disturbances in his heart rhythm. 
</P>
<P>
Snow, who is a mayoral candidate in the March 7 elections, was described in a 
press release Tuesday as "fully alert and conversational (and) anxious to get 
back to work." He has missed the last two City Council meetings as a result of 
his illness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
