<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
APPOINTMENT FOR HOTEL PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a move to speed planning for a proposed luxury hotel at the defunct 
Marineland in Rancho Palos Verdes, John E. Corcoran, 45, has been named vice 
president for development of the Monaghan Co., which purchased the 102-acre 
seaside property in May, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Corcoran, who was general manager of Marineland when it closed, has been a 
consultant on the project since its inception. 
</P>
<P>
The city in November sent back two envelopes of documents to Arizona-based 
developer James Monaghan, complaining of delays and missed deadlines in the 
hotel planning process. The city invited Monaghan to submit complete 
applications later. 
</P>
<P>
Corcoran said his new position gives him "authority . . . to head up the 
project and make decisions. . . . Part of this is to speed up the project and 
coordinate all different design phases." 
</P>
<P>
Corcoran declined, however, to predict when a completed project and application 
package will be given to the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
