<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCILMAN BELSKY TO BE HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Rolling Hills Estates Councilman Jerome Belsky will be honored at a 
dinner Wednesday at Los Verdes Country Club, 7000 W. Los Verdes Drive, Rancho 
Palos Verdes. 
</P>
<P>
After 12 years on the council, Belsky, 70, was forced from office in a bitter 
recall election in November. 
</P>
<P>
"This is being organized by friends of Jerry's who would like to show him 
recognition," said Priscilla Regur, dinner organizer. The cost is $25 per 
person. People who wish to attend may call Regur at 375-4477. 
</P>
<P>
Three candidates -- William Ailor, Jacqueline McGuire and Robert Schachter -- 
are running in a special election March 21 to fill the remainder of Belsky's 
term, which ends in November. 
</P>
