<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: PARAMOUNT; 
</P>
<P>
AWARD-WINNING CIVIC CLEANUP PROGRAM TO END 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After two years, the city's "Let's Get Paramount Neighborhoods Lookin' Good" 
program, which targeted specific residential areas for cleanup, is coming to an 
end. 
</P>
<P>
The program, which used volunteers, residents and city staff members to fix up 
and repair areas at no cost to residents, ends Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Since the program began, about 2,000 volunteers worked more than 8,000 hours 
cleaning 1,000 properties, painting almost 700 homes and removing 3,400 tons of 
debris, said Patrick West, deputy city manager. 
</P>
<P>
The Lookin' Good program was one of three municipal projects that helped the 
city win the All-American City Award from the National Civic League last year. 
Paramount was one of 10 cities to be honored by the league for solving major 
community problems or issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
