<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAME PROMOTES SOBER PROM/GRADUATION 1989 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alcohol- and other drug-related crashes are the leading cause of death for 
young people between the ages of 16 and 24. Graduation is just around the 
corner, and this time of celebration can quickly turn to tragedy. In fact, 13 
young people died in such crashes in Ventura County last year. 
</P>
<P>
Local initiatives such as Operation Graduation are making a difference in 
eliminating this tragedy. 
</P>
<P>
We can use your help to make prom/graduation 1989 a great success. 
</P>
<P>
Attending a basketball game between the "Court Jesters" -- the Ventura County 
district attorney's office -- and the "Donut Dunkers" -- the California Highway 
Patrol -- at the Buena High School gym at 6 p.m. Saturday, Jan. 21, is one way 
you can help and have some family fun at the same time. All proceeds will be 
designated to Sober Prom/Graduation 1989. Tickets are $2.50 and are available 
at the door. 
</P>
<P>
KAY HINE 
</P>
<P>
Mothers Against Drunk Driving 
</P>
<P>
Ventura 
</P>
