<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
2 ARRESTED IN THREAT TO POTENTIAL WITNESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two gang members, one a juvenile and the other an adult, were arrested after 
threatening a 15-year-old who was scheduled to be a witness at a gang-shooting 
trial, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Santos Manuel Lopez, 20, of Costa Mesa was arrested Wednesday, and a 
17-year-old Back Bay High School student was arrested Tuesday. Both were taken 
into custody on suspicion of dissuading a witness by threat, a felony, Costa 
Mesa Police Sgt. Ron Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old was "approached in person by an adult and a juvenile male who 
said they were Blood gang members out of Santa Ana," Smith said. "They 
threatened him with physical harm if he appeared to testify against their 
fellow Bloods." 
</P>
<P>
The teen-ager did not have to testify at the Tuesday trial because the two gang 
members eventually pleaded guilty after plea bargains were arranged, Smith 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Five adults and four juveniles were arrested in October for a gang-related 
fistfight and shooting at a shopping center. One teen-ager was injured in the 
fistfight, but no one was shot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
