<HEADLINE>
<P>
RITES FRIDAY FOR EX-GOP CHAIR E.F. WARD JR. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TYLER L. CHIN, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Memorial services will be conducted on Friday for Edward F. Ward Jr., former 
chairman of the Orange County Republican Central Committee. 
</P>
<P>
Ward, 57, of Palm Desert and Newport Beach, died of brain cancer Sunday at Hoag 
Memorial Hospital Presbyterian in Newport Beach. Ward, who lived in Orange 
County for many years, was a former administrative assistant to then 
Assemblyman Robert E. Badham (R-Newport Beach). 
</P>
<P>
Born on Nov. 27, 1931, in San Francisco, Ward was graduated cum laude from 
Stanford University in 1953 with a degree in political science. He participated 
in the university's ROTC program and was commissioned a second lieutenant in 
the U.S. Air Force upon graduation. 
</P>
<P>
Honorably discharged in 1955, Ward began working as an insurance agent for Jay 
&amp; Renfro of Newport Beach. Between 1971 and July, 1977, he served as 
corporate secretary and director of the Willard Co., an Orange County 
boat-building firm. 
</P>
<P>
In 1974, Ward was elected chairman of the Orange County Republican Central 
Committee, a position he held for about 7 1/2 months until he resigned, citing 
personal business pressures. 
</P>
<P>
Before his election as committee chairman, he served as administrative 
assistant to Badham for about 5 years. 
</P>
<P>
Ward also was an original member of the Orange County Sheriff's Advisory 
Council, which was formed in 1980. He is survived by his wife, Jean Lea Reed 
Ward; daughters Calene Fleurke and Lea Ward and granddaughters Adrienne and 
Xandria Fleurke. 
</P>
<P>
Memorial services will be conducted at Newport Harbor Lutheran Church in 
Newport Beach. The family requests that any contributions be made to the Orange 
County Sheriff's Advisory Project 999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Edward F. Ward Jr. in 1975. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
