<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BREA-OLINDA STAVES OFF WESTERN RALLY, WINS AT THE BUZZER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aaron Charlton scored at the buzzer to give Brea-Olinda High School a 68-66 
victory over Western Wednesday in an Orange League basketball game at Brea. 
</P>
<P>
The Wildcats (13-6, 2-1) led, 66-64, but Western's Ed Serranno tied the score 
with 7 seconds left on a layup. After a time out, Charlton took the inbounds 
pass and drove through the middle for a layup to win the game. 
</P>
<P>
The Pioneers (12-4, 1-2) trailed, 50-35, at the start of the third quarter but 
rallied behind the shooting of Brian Baber, who scored 12 of his 14 points in 
the final quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Brea led, 27-24, at halftime and outscored Western, 23-11 in the third quarter. 
Matt Chamberlain scored 12 of his 17 points in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Keith Walker scored 30 points for the Wildcats. 
</P>
<P>
Joe Romero each scored 14 points for Western. 
</P>
<P>
In other Orange League games: 
</P>
<P>
Savanna 61, Magnolia 39 -- Tim Tillman scored 15 points and pulled down 12 
rebounds to lead host Savanna (17-1, 3-0). Jurry Jones led Magnolia (8-7, 2-1) 
with 10. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 47, Anaheim 46 -- Richard Tibbie scored 2 free throws with 38 seconds 
remaining to give Valencia a 47-44 lead. Mark Miller scored 14 for Valencia 
(4-8, 1-2). Danny Castro led Anaheim (7-9, 0-3) with 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
Foothill 53, Canyon 44 -- Mark Wilkinson scored 25 points and Corey Parker 13 
for Foothill (10-9, 2-2). Canyon is 11-8, 1-3. 
</P>
<P>
El Modena 79, Santa Ana Valley 63 -- Robbie Pietsch had 24 points and 26 
rebounds to lead host El Modena (14-5, 3-1). Chuck Speen scored 31 points for 
Santa Ana Valley (14-6, 2-2). 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 64, Villa Park 48 -- Oscar Wilson scored 26 points and had 11 
rebounds to lead host Santa Ana (15-5, 3-1). Chris Johnson had 16 points and 
Chris Kirby had 11 to lead Villa Park (9-8, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 69, Katella 56 -- Mark Johnson and Mike Flowers scored 20 points each 
to lead host Cypress (9-9, 4-0). Brian Yourstone and Tim Hall led Katella 
(6-10, 2-3) with 11 points each. 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 73, Loara 53 -- Matt Luke scored 8 points in the first quarter as El 
Dorado led, 20-12. Luke finished with 18 points and 15 rebounds. Mike Renaud 
and Mike Bradach added 15 each for El Dorado (14-4, 4-0). Tes Whitlock led 
Loara (2-13, 0-4) with 25. 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 62, Esperanza 59 (OT) -- Los Alamitos (7-12, 2-2) trailed by 14 
points with 5 minutes to play but battled back. Ted LaBouff, a 5-11 guard who 
came up from the junior varsity for the game, hit a 3-point shot with 5 seconds 
remaining to tie the score at 59. His 3 free throws accounted for the only 
points in overtime. LaBouff finished with 11 points and teammate Mike Wilson 
scored 25. Greg Pope led Esperanza (6-12, 0-4) with 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
Troy 54, Buena Park 38 -- Richard Wesley scored 15 points to lead host Troy 
(6-10, 1-3). Mike Abbott scored 10 points for the Warriors, who outscored the 
Coyotes (0-13, 0-4), 23-7, in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 68, Sonora 63 -- Pete Bach scored 21 points to lead host Fullerton 
(11-5, 4-0). Matt Recktenwald had 21 points for Sonora (6-11, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 78, Costa Mesa 60 -- Chris Sheff scored 27 points and Pat Nelson 
scored 23 to lead Laguna Hills (11-6, 3-0). Tim Nguyen led Costa Mesa (2-13, 
0-3) with 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
Trabuco Hills 74, Laguna Beach 49 -- Center Rick Swanwick scored 18 points, 
grabbed 19 rebounds and blocked 6 shots as the Mustangs (11-5, 3-0) remained in 
a first-place tie with Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 74, Orange 59 -- Herman Cohen scored 18 points to lead host 
Woodbridge (4-10, 2-1). John Rodriguez scored 22 points for Orange (2-12, 0-3). 
</P>
<P>
In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 62, Marina 56 -- Tom Weaver scored 18 points and Derrick 
Corcoran 16 to lead host Fountain Valley (16-2, 4-0). Thi Nguyen scored 16 
points for Marina (8-11, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 82, Westminster 44 -- Scott Drake scored 17 points to lead 
Huntington Beach (8-9, 3-1) at Westminster. Jeff Long scored 14 points for the 
Oilers. Westminster is 3-13, 0-4. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 55, Edison 51 -- Todd Norman scored 19 points to lead host Ocean 
View (12-6, 2-2). Bill Martineau scored 16 for Edison (9-11, 1-3). 
</P>
