<P>
Aerojet Ordnance said the prospect of federal budget cuts has prompted a 
decision by the defense contractor to close its headquarters in Tustin and 
transfer all 108 employees to Downey by summer. "In light of the defense 
picture, this is a really good business move for us. We are just maximizing our 
